.TH MYSTIFY 6 "June 2026" "mystify 0.1.0" "XScreenSaver display hacks"
.SH NAME
mystify \- nostalgic bouncing wire polygons for XScreenSaver
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mystify
.RB [ \-display
display]
.RB [ \-root ]
.RB [ \-window ]
.RB [ \-window-id
id]
.RB [ \-delay
microseconds]
.RB [ \-polys
number]
.RB [ \-points
number]
.RB [ \-trails
number]
.RB [ \-speed
number]
.RB [ \-thickness
pixels]
.RB [ \-colors
number]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mystify
animates deforming wire polygons whose corners move independently and change
speed when they bounce from the edges of the window.
.PP
It is inspired by the Windows 95/98 "Mystify Your Mind" screensaver. Instead
of clearing or redrawing the whole frame, it draws one new wire and erases
only the oldest retained wire with black. This is both lightweight and
responsible for the characteristic tiny black gaps where old and new wires
cross.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-root
Draw on the root window.
.TP
.B \-window
Create a normal 800 by 600 test window. This is the default when no root or
external window is supplied.
.TP
.BI \-window-id " id"
Draw into an existing X window. The environment variable
.B XSCREENSAVER_WINDOW
is also recognized.
.TP
.BI \-delay " microseconds"
Delay between frames. Default: 30000.
.TP
.BI \-polys " number"
Number of independently moving polygons. Default: 2.
.TP
.BI \-points " number"
Corners per polygon. Default: 4.
.TP
.BI \-trails " number"
Number of old wires retained behind each leading wire. Default: 5.
.TP
.BI \-speed " number"
Maximum corner velocity. Default: 17 pixels per frame.
.TP
.BI \-thickness " pixels"
Line thickness. Default: 1.
.TP
.BI \-colors " number"
Number of hue steps in the allocated palette. Default: 64.
.TP
.BI \-seed " number"
Use a deterministic random seed.
.TP
.BI \-frames " number"
Exit after a number of frames. Intended for testing.
.TP
.B \-self-test
Run non-graphical internal tests and exit.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B DISPLAY
Default X display.
.TP
.B XSCREENSAVER_WINDOW
Existing target window supplied by XScreenSaver.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR xscreensaver (1),
.BR xscreensaver-settings (1),
.BR X (7)
